HEADWORD: Phenalgin
<hw>Phe*nal"gin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Phen</ets>yl
+ an<ets>alg</ets>etic + <ets>-in</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Pharm.)</fld>
<def>An ammoniated compound of phenyl and acetamide, used as an
analgesic and antipyretic. It resembles phenacetin in its therapeutic
action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

